        <h1>Wage and personnel policy </h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"></div>
        
            <p class="textIngress">The Ministry is responsible for the state's central employer function. 
This responsibility includes drawing up the framework for the execution and development of the function as employer in state enterprises. 

</p>
        
            
        <div class="descriptionTextFull"><p>The Ministry enters into agreements with the main trade union cooperative organisations on issues of wages and working conditions, as well as managing the laws and regulations in the state labour regulation field applying to the entire state administration. </p></div>
